11/03/2004
ATHENS, Greece -- Newly-appointed Prime Minister Costas Karamanlis will meet with International Olympic Committee (IOC) President Jacques Rogge on Saturday (13 March) to discuss preparations for the Summer Olympics in Athens. The IOC has issued a statement commending Karamanlis' decision to temporarily head the ministry of culture so he can personally oversee preparations. (ANA, MPA - 10/03/04)
